===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|口|乞|c1=s|c2=p|t1=mouth|ls=psc}} – "to stutter".

The phonetic component could add part of the meaning since it has the phonetically borrowed meaning of "begging" (i.e., trying to talk but with difficulties).

According to folk etymologies, {{zh-l|*乞}} in this character indicates that, while stuttering, less air comes from the mouth (compare {{zh-l|*气}}, which has more trails). However, this is incorrect. {{lang|zh|乞}} is simply a variant of {{lang|zh|气}}, originally meaning "air" and later borrowed to indicate "begging".

